<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-518-806  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 518 806.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  August 14 1989 v23 n33 p36(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Folio Views can deliver on text retrieval. (Folio Corp. FolioViews text-retrieval software) (evaluation)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Folio Corp's $495 Folio Views is a powerful text-retrieval systembest suited to applications in which the user needs access tosmall portions of large files, such as reference books, on-linetechnical manuals, literary research, and legal work.andP;  It is basedon 'underhead indexing,' a proprietary indexing system in whichthe user imports a text file to an 'infobase' that holds both thecompressed text and the index.andP;  Folio Views has a stand-aloneprogram called Create for reading the prepared text files andplacing them in the infobase.andP;  It has a comprehensive set ofsearch tools, including scrollable list of every word in theinfobase and a 'view' window what contains the results of eachsearch.andP;  The user can also add cross-referenced, hypertext-stylelinks.andP;  Folio Views is fast, easy to use, and has excellentdocumentation.andP;  The company offers free technical support.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Folio Corp. (products).andO;Product:   Folio Views (Computer program).andO;Topic:     Information Storage and RetrievalSoftware PackagesEvaluationData Management.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>